-- Greek Police Arrest 20 After Takeover of Athens Radio Station
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2012-01-10T16:13:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/greek-police-arrest-20-after-takeover-of-athens-radio-station.html
Twenty people were arrested today
after protesters occupied a private radio station in  Athens ,
according to a text message from Greek police.  A group of about 30 people briefly took over the premises
of the Flash radio station, interrupting broadcasts, state-run
Athens News Agency reported.  Members of the group, which ANA described as anarchists,
read out a statement of support for terror group Revolutionary
Struggle and referred to the causes of the economic crisis in
 Greece , ANA said, without saying how it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Stoukas in Athens at 
 astoukas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
